reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome travel knife
reviews.reviewText: I wanted some cutlery to take on vacations with us. We normally shop for some groceries and our kids are fruit obsessed. This allows us to buy food at the store and prep it in our condo/hotel so we don’t have to eat out every meal. The blade was sharp and the action is smooth. The wood color is so rich and the little pouch is a nice touch, as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I wanted
reviews.reviewText: Sometimes when out of town visiting relatives and friends I get called to KP duty which I am happy and honored to help out in the kitchen. Once in the kitchen and looking things to use to cut food into smaller pieces or that can be used for peeling vegies....I am usually at a loss. Most of the time the selection of knives and peelers leaves a lot to be desired. Most are dull making the work to be done more difficult. (We have a good knife set in the home and I maintain an edge on all of them.)Out of frustration I put together a small traveling culinary set consisting of a vegetable peeler, paring knife. kitchen shears, and this folding chef's knife. Perfect, now am ready to visit and help in the kitchen.The quality of the knife is topnotch, it locks safely in place, and is easy to fold up. Razor sharp it is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great value, may need some initial tuning
reviews.reviewText: Just received this item, review is based off first-impressions:TLDR: a fine knife, fit for light carving and prep work. May need some initial tuning to secure handle scales and straighten the blade, but overall I'm pleased with the quality (especially for the price).Knife arrived in a classy box, contained withing a faux-burlap bag (as pictured in product description). The knife as a whole is fairly sizeable, with an appropriate handle to control the size of the blade.The mechanism and lock are as expected - I may not trust them with my life necessarily, but they will keep the knife in place well-enough for the intended labor. Blade is razor-sharp, exceeding my initial expectations for a blade in this price range. Blade tapers to an exceptionally thin primary bevel, with short secondary bevel facilitating the sharp edge. Due to that thin taper, the blade may be slightly warped (will need to get it to the work bench to know for sure). If that's the case, because the blase is 440 stainless steel, I feel would feel comfortable lightly twisting the blade back straight, if necessary.Due to the thin edge and relatively soft steel (stainless vs. high-carbon), plus the liner-lock keeping the blade open, this knife is not well-suited for heavy work / chopping. I would use this for paring (despite the blade shape) and light carving / light prep. For non-kitchen work, use extra caution when handling a blade of this size / sharpness / shape (unconventional for EDC applications). Remember that the thin edge is not suited for heavy work.Handle scales are olive wood, with a fine finish to keep the wood sealed. One of the scales on my knife was loose, and showed evidence of being patched with a shim to mitigate the effect of the poor fit (pictured). Scale still shifts near the top (by the top of the scale), which I'm hoping will be solved by either tightening the star-screw and / or a dab of glue.Overall, this is a good product, which I will be happy to utilize in my kitchen. My only complaints are the one poorly-fitted scale and the slight warping of the blade, which are both fixable. All things considered, this is an excellent product, and I would have been happy to receive this as a gift. Consider this for any chef in your life, especially if they like knives.

reviews.reviewText: I shop for price and quality and this knife is good around the kitchen although I keep it in my 24 hr bag. Sharp as the day is long and easy to put an edge on when needed. reviews.reviewText: I wasn't expecting much from this, I just wanted a portable knife for cooking while camping. However out of the box you can tell this knife was well crafted. Not only is it solid construction, but it is razor sharp. I pride myself on keeping my kitchen knives on a razors edge, however this rivaled everything I had out of the box. Honestly for the price I am extremely impressed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Portable, sharp, sturdy, foldable
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to cut fruit at my bar. Seriously, even the snottiest of craft cocktailers are terrible with knives. Like they've never worked in a restaurant and not heard chefs scream about knife care.I've tried bring in good knives and insist they be sheathed when not in use and only used on wood or plastic boards. They will use them on metal in a pinch. They will store them, blade down, in a metal shaker with other metal tools.While they saw through citrus with a brand new cheap, short, lightweight paring knife I'm getting the job done faster and with far less effort.It's not the greatest knife ever, for sure. It's not forged, the bolster isn't, well, there, so not great for a pinch grip. But using it only for bar fruit and keeping it away from the abuses of others I think it will last me a good, long time.And the foldable.... It just makes it so much easier. It fits in a small pocket in my bag. It can stay there and I don't have to take it out to make room for real life when I'm not at work so I don't have to worry about forgetting it.

調理用の折りたたみナイフを探していて購入。先日まで5,200円だったものが、3,000円弱になっていたので購入。一通り使ってみたので良い点、気になる点をまとめます。【良い点◎】1.薄刃で包丁に近い感覚で使用できるため、非常に調理に向いています。(ただしハンドルが大きいので、押切りをすると指がまな板に当たるため慣れが必要)2.この価格で440A鋼材（モーラナイフ コンパニオンの12c27と同等クラス）を使っているのが好印象。3.開閉がしやすく、ロック機構もガッチリしていてガタ付きがほぼ無いので安全。【気になる点×】1.ハンドル材のウッドが角ばっていて痛い→自分で削って当たりを良くしました。2.重量が重い→実測170g強あるため、キャンプ中にポケットに入れていると存在感がある。3.重量バランスがあまり良くない→ハンドル部が大きく、刃先との重量配分があまり良くないです。家庭用の包丁は刃先に重量が振られているため、食材を切る際に自重でスルスル切れますが、このナイフでは使い方を少々意識する必要があります。4.ハンドルの金属部にバリや合わせの乱れがある→使用中に指に引っかかる感触があるため、ここもヤスリで微調整が必要そうです。【総評】3,000円以内で買えるのであれば非常に優秀でおすすめできます。5,000円を超えるとちょっと割高感が否めないかな…比較検討していたフェデカ（10,000円弱）の方が、高くてもその分の所有欲や、高級感を満たしてくれると思います。この価格（3,000円）でこのクオリティが手に入るのであれば、とてもおすすめできる商品と言えます。
